  <refnamediv>
    <refname>plsiread</refname>

    <refpurpose>Read data from a file for training for the probabilistic
    latent semantic indexing approach.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>

    <synopsis>[docnum wordnum matrix] = plsiread(filename, issparse)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>filename</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Name of the file containing the training data.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>issparse</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Whether the data in the file uses a sparse way (i.e.:
          wordid:count). 1 if the file is in the sparse style; 0 if
          not.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>docnum</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Number of the documents.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>wordnum</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>Number of the words.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
        <term>matrix</term>

        <listitem>
          <para>The term-document matrix whose size is (docnum by
          wordnum).</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>

  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>

    <para>plsiread reads training data from a given file into a Scilab matrix.
    The outputs can be used as inputs of plsitrain.</para>
  </refsection>

